        <p data-uuid="e44ab167e9c14265917c1d61ff1b458b">Penn named the capital of his colony Philadelphia, which means “the city of brotherly love.” In 1682 the Duke of York sold Penn a region to the south of Pennsylvania. This area, called Delaware, remained part of Pennsylvania until 1776.</p>
